Ephemerides calculation for spacecrafts and artificial satellites.

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    SatelliteEphem
    This class implements a very simple theory of the motion of artificial satellites.
    SatelliteEphemElement
    Convenient class to store results of ephemeris of artificial satellites.
    SatelliteOrbitalElement
    An adequate class for storing orbital elements of artificial satellites.
    SDP4_SGP4
    The SDP4_SGP4 class is a base class to calculate ephemeris for an artificial Earth satellite, using the SGP4 and SDP4 models.
    SDP8_SGP8
    The SDP8_SGP8 class is a base class to calculate ephemeris for an artificial Earth satellite, using the SGP8 and SDP8 models.
    Spacecraft
    This class provides data for most of the space probes launched so far, as well as methods for ephemeris calculations.

Package jparsec.ephem.probes Description

Ephemerides calculation for spacecrafts and artificial satellites.

The approximate position of different spacecrafts can be calculated using orbital elements from JPL. This requires the corresponding set of orbital elements in certain format, available as a JPARSEC dependency.
